  Sounds like the same thing that happened to me on the way to the Classic
this year. I started to loose number 2 exhaust valve. I had to stop every 50
to 100 miles to readjust it, finally took the roller tip adjuster off and
put in a regular screw and got more miles out of it, made it 500 miles that
weekend till there was no more valve adjustment left. Am pulling the engine
tomorrow to pull the head to get it fixed so I can drive to Familian Fest
this weekend.

ronnie

ps. Love those Manley valves, all the abuse and they still don't break, just
hope we can weld up the valve seat base. I am sure I hammered it way into
the head!!

